&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a remote position and can be located anywhere in the US.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will my role be?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end Board EPM solution implementations, including requirements gathering, design, configuration, testing, deployment, and user enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate FP&amp;amp;A processes (Budgeting, Forecasting, Consolidations, Reporting) into scalable Board models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate client workshops, discovery sessions, and process design interviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project timelines, deliverables, and client expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with PMO, solution architects, and technical team members to ensure successful delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create executive-level documentation, dashboards, and training materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement of delivery methodology and internal accelerators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s required?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum 4 years experience implementing Board EPM solution in a consulting environment (required)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FP&amp;amp;A experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of corporate budgeting/forecasting, financial modeling, and performance reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate business requirements into functional system design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel and data modeling skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of managerial accounting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
